<p>
    <br>
</p>
<p>So in summary, the story thus far is this. Â 2011 saw retirement arrive for us both; Â Rosemarie from her house renovation activities and John from corporate life. Â The first task was to downsize from the largeÂ family home of the last
    twenty yearsÂ on Sydney's North Shore. Â This proved more difficult than we expected and after two years, punctuated by bothÂ a long trip through Outback Australia and a visit toÂ China, we headed to LondonÂ in March 2013 intending
    to stay for a couple of years while tenants in the houseÂ helped us defer the downsizing plan. Â We did have seriousÂ thoughts of living in a narrowboat, roaming the amazing UK canal network, but insteadÂ our 7.5mÂ French motorhome
    proved to beÂ the ideal accommodation and transport for overÂ 20,000 kms of European meandering.</p>
<p>
    <br>
</p>
<p>We've camped since before we were married and since then have always enjoyed the mobile and outdoor life, whether it be bicycle or motorcycle touring, family holiday or outback (4WD) camping. Â By comparison our motorhome lifestyle in Europe feels
    like soft luxury camping so it's no surprise that we're become very partial to this lifestyle.
    <br>
</p>
<p>
    <br>
</p>
<p>We've had some great travels in mainland Europe, spending time in the Czech Republic and Austria but mostly
    in France, Germany, Belgium and the Netherlands in which four countries we've alsoÂ done a lot of cycling. Â Highlights include the MotoGPÂ in Brno, the Berlin Marathon,Â a rally with the German Vintage Cycling Club, tandem rallies
