    if possible.
    <br>
</p>
<p>
    <br>
</p>
<p>To explain why London is our EuropeanÂ base,Â for those of our more recently acquired friends, the one-word answer is children. Â Amy, then Louisa, then Tim one by oneÂ from the late nineties to the late noughties, migrated toÂ London;
    Â their moves readily facilitated by dual nationality. Â While theyÂ remainÂ Australians to the core, not even Sydney can beat London as a location for jobs, nightlife and travel. Â And the acquisition of British partners hasÂ helped
    keep them there, despite the weather.</p>
<p>
    <br>
</p>
<p>In August 2016 we upgraded our motorhome to a larger German model moreÂ suitable for quite some more years of this most enjoyableÂ touringÂ lifestyle. Ultimately, no doubt, we'll have to work out whether a more permanent residence is required,
    and whether it's going to be in Europe or Australia.Â We think that might take a little while.</p>
